.SH NAME
\fBchar\fP(3f) - [FORTRAN:INTRINSIC:CHARACTER] Character conversion function

.SH SYNTAX
result = \fBchar\fP(i [, kind])
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBchar\fP(i [, kind]) returns the character represented by the integer I.
.SS   ARGUMENTS

.TP
.B I
The type shall be INTEGER.
.TP
.B KIND
(Optional) An INTEGER initialization
expression indicating the kind parameter of the result.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The return value is of type \fBcharacter\fP(1)
.SH EXAMPLE
Sample program:
.PP
.nf
.fam C
    program demo_char
    implicit none
    integer :: i = 74
    character(1) :: c
        c = char(i)
        print *, i, c ! returns 'J'
    end program demo_char

.fam T
.fi
